Encode:

yep that was loads of work, its still the hq mic that was used for previous releases, but its worth cleaning it through.
there is no laughing,no metallic noise, no music problems, could pass as a line.
i cleaned it trough removed all kind of noise,hiss and played with the freq. and it came out really nice.

Bida already tried syncing it, but there are lots of oos spots, the major at the 33 min mark, where 2 minutes arent sync at all, followed by a cut with a russian word cut in, after that 50-100 ms moved around making it not lipsync.
so i had to fix all that, everything is lipsync now, also the russian word is removed.
whilest i was in the mood i removed the russian guy talking in the endcredits, which ruins the whole retail-experience of the track.. 
after having that nice audio i entered it back into the russian 5.1 track, and hear ya go

for the video, the colours on the disc were off a lot, tried a couple different approaches, till i found a nice colouring for the complete movie, the rest as usual, brightness,sharpness and denoise

got very nice,
will perfectly do till bluray comes along
this is the version to get guys 

